name: language_html_data_active_single_quoted_attribute_throw
description: |
  This is the single-quoted-attribute counterpart to the double-quoted breakout.
  Unsafe interpolation creates an SVG whose load handler throws the stable
  canary error; correct context-aware encoding preserves the bytes as data.

  The handler does not access the network, DOM application state, or storage.
format: utf8-strip
decode-as: ascii
pair:
  - with: ../attribute/single-quote.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "language"
  - "html"
  - "xss"
  - "xss-data"
  - "active-xss-canary"
  - "html-attribute-context"
  - "single-quote"
  - "attribute-injection"
  - "throws-error"
---
'><svg onload="throw new Error('trickydata-xss-canary')"></svg><x x='
